post_text:
Practice is important and getting better is too, but so is being a kid. Too often they grow up too fast and don't actually get to enjoy being at this stage in their lives. So, tomorrow we have no practice. We were supposed to work for 2 hours, but kids need to be kids.

Kids are not tools to win a contest or game. Kids are not meant to be used up and thrown away when you find someone better. Kids are meant to be cherished and worked with and valued, regardless of status, skill, or perceived intelligence. While you can't reach them all, we in the White Oak Band Department try our best to do just that.

Performances will come and go. Contests will come and go. Go outside. Spend time TALKING to a friend. Spend time TALKING to your family. Enjoy these moments before the hectic rush of school starts. You won't get them back.

Just please spend at least a little time on your horn before Monday. A few minutes on a countermarch wouldn't hurt some of you either!

For the private tour of the Capitol on the evening of July 3rd the following guidelines will need to be strictly followed:

From the office of Louie Gohmert, US House, TX District 1

The following items are strictly prohibited in the Capitol, including the Capitol Visitor Center:

Liquid, including water
Food or beverages of any kind, including fruit and unopened packaged food
Aerosol containers
Non-aerosol spray (Prescriptions for medical needs are permitted.)
Any pointed object, e.g. knitting needles and letter openers (Pens and pencils are permitted.)
Any bag larger than 18" wide x 14" high x 8.5" deep
Electric stun guns, martial arts weapons or devices
Guns, replica guns, ammunition, and fireworks
Knives of any size
Mace and pepper spray
Razors and box cutters

Please note that the U.S. Capitol Police are authorized to make exceptions if a prohibited item is determined to be necessary and required to serve child care, medical or other special needs.

post_text:
The Last Band Room Visit

Before you leave the band room for the last time, stop and take a look around for just one moment. These four walls have seen you at your worst and at your best, they had watched families created, and families fall apart, they have seen love between two people and one sided crushes, they have seen your most joyous days and maybe melancholy ones, they have seen the person when you walked in for the first time and now have seen the person you are for the last time. And when you turn back and walk the the halls for the very last time, know that the walls are silently weeping and maybe you are too because you both realized that in order to go somewhere in life, you must have home.

Thank you class of 2018. You'll be greatly missed.

Mr. Steele

Wednesday April 6th both of the bands in the High School (Symphonic, and Wind Ensemble) will perform at Mt. Pleasant High School in their auditorium. The schedule for the day is as follows:

7:50 arrive for 1st period and begin loading equipment

8:15 depart White Oak High School

9:15 arrive Mt. Pleasant High School

9:20 Symphonic Band Warmup

10:00 Symphonic Band Perform

10:30 Symphonic Band Sightread

10:50 Wind Ensemble Warmup

11:30 Wind Ensemble Perform

12:00 Wind Ensemble Sightread

1:00 Depart for White Oak stop for lunch possibly

3:30 Arrive at White Oak High School

Admission is free to the public and we would love for as many of you than can make it to please try and be there. Thank you for all of your support, and if you have any questions please let me know.

steelej@woisd.net

We will be sending calendars home this week with your student. Each student in HS and MS will receive a minimum of 2 calendars to sell at $10 each. For each calendar sold, your child will receive 1 Band Booster point. If you would like more than the 2 minimum, please let us know ASAP. All money and/or unsold calendars must be turned in by Monday, January 11 or the cost of the calendars will be taken from your child's account. Thanks for always supporting our efforts and I hope you enjoy this year's calendar. Please email me with any questions you might have.
Julie
WO Band Booster Secretary
Julie@rrhilllaw.com

November 5, 2015 at 1:55 PM ·

Now that State is behind us, Melissa is working diligently on getting the calendars ready to sale. She is in the process of sifting through the thousands of pictures she has taken of the students this year and getting them edited. Currently she has 4 spots remaining for any businesses that would like to place an ad. These ads are a banner style, month ad and are $250 ea. If you have a business and would like to place an ad, or if you know of anybody that would like to place one, please contact Melissa. Her contact information is listed below.

ALSO, new this year are the ads the High School and Middle School Band students and their families can purchase their student. These can be used as they wish, with multiple students, or just one. The deadline to purchase a student ad is November 10th so please get with Melissa ASAP.
The prices for the student ads will be:
1/6 page $25
1/4 page $40
1/2 page $75
Full page $150

Please contact Melissa Schaetz through facebook or email: MelissaSchaetz@gmail.com

White Oak Band Boosters
October 23, 2015 at 4:05 PM ·

****UPDATE**** Plans can still change at any minute. However, as of now we are more than likely going to be marching in the practice field facility at Carthage. Mr. Steele has emailed asking politely that people do not attend. We Booster Officers are asking no one enter the area to watch the band march. There is literally NO WHERE to sit and see the routine. The judges will be on scaffolding over the drum pit. Being this close will already throw the kids off, we don't need to make it worse on them by being in their faces, no matter how good our intentions. We are scheduled to march at 10:15. We will be buying the band pizza to eat right after, then we will possibly come back home for a few hours to rest, returning for announcements and finals. We are excited to announce that we will be working with a new technology company called "Music Prodigy". post_text: Please review this information
shared_text:
White Oak Band Boosters published a note.
January 15, 2015 at 8:16 PM ·

Booster Minutes 01.12.15
White Oak Band Booster Meeting Minutes
Jan. 12, 2015, 6:30 pm
Board Members Present: Donna Jennings, Tina Moyers


Topics discussed:  Disney Trip, Chaperones, Trip Payments, Calendars, Basketball Concession, Booster Treasurer, Sweet Auction


Calendar:  The calendars or the money for them is due!!  Please turn in one or the other.  Over 100 students have still failed to turn theirs in.  Please take care of this ASAP.


Disney Trip:  Mr. Steele sent email during Christmas break with information.   Please refer to it for details.  We are still not sure of hotel yet.  There has been a park added to make 4 parks we will be visiting.  A meal trip plan was discussed, but it ended up being too costly.  The band directors may possibly hold the students money and divvy out a set amount each day.  This will help ensure we have no starving children or broke chaperones (from loans).  Each meal averages $10 at the park.  So please plan accordingly.  Deposits have now been made on the busses and trip.  Any payments made toward the trip are NON-REFUNDABLE.  The itinerary is not set in stone yet and could still change.


Online Trip Payments:  We have uploaded our instructional video to YouTube. This video will show you step by step how to update your Charms Information and how make your trip payments online as well. Please remember that our trip payment deadlines are approaching. We hope the added connivence of online works well for many of you. This will help you make sure that your student doesn't lose a check, lose the cash or forget to turn things in on time. To view the video click the link:

http://youtu.be/ZmCFnmOodh8


Chaperones:  Once we have the first payment in, we will have a better idea of how many students will be going.  Once we know this, we will then be able to decide how many chaperones we will need.  Mrs. Jennings has a list for parents wanting to be considered as a chaperone.  Please contact her if you are wanting to be added to that list.  This does not ensure your being chosen.  Mr. Steele will choose chaperones from that list.


Sweet Music Auction:  Currently set for Feb. 28, but that date could change.


Treasurer:  Michele Cloer has stepped down, Mrs. Jennings will take over those duties for the rest of the school year.


Basketball Concession:  Please stay and help clean up at the end of your shift.  We have had an issue with students leaving before the concession stand has been closed down.  Stay until all the work is done.

Booster Minutes 01.12.15
White Oak Band Booster Meeting Minutes
Jan. 12, 2015, 6:30 pm
Board Members Present: Donna Jennings, Tina Moyers


Topics discussed:  Disney Trip, Chaperones, Trip Payments, Calendars, Basketball Concession, Booster Treasurer, Sweet Auction


Calendar:  The calendars or the money for them is due!!  Please turn in one or the other.  Over 100 students have still failed to turn theirs in.  Please take care of this ASAP.


Disney Trip:  Mr. Steele sent email during Christmas break with information.   Please refer to it for details.  We are still not sure of hotel yet.  There has been a park added to make 4 parks we will be visiting.  A meal trip plan was discussed, but it ended up being too costly.  The band directors may possibly hold the students money and divvy out a set amount each day.  This will help ensure we have no starving children or broke chaperones (from loans).  Each meal averages $10 at the park.  So please plan accordingly.  Deposits have now been made on the busses and trip.  Any payments made toward the trip are NON-REFUNDABLE.  The itinerary is not set in stone yet and could still change.


Online Trip Payments:  We have uploaded our instructional video to YouTube. This video will show you step by step how to update your Charms Information and how make your trip payments online as well. Please remember that our trip payment deadlines are approaching. We hope the added connivence of online works well for many of you. This will help you make sure that your student doesn't lose a check, lose the cash or forget to turn things in on time. To view the video click the link:

http://youtu.be/ZmCFnmOodh8


Chaperones:  Once we have the first payment in, we will have a better idea of how many students will be going.  Once we know this, we will then be able to decide how many chaperones we will need.  Mrs. Jennings has a list for parents wanting to be considered as a chaperone.  Please contact her if you are wanting to be added to that list.  This does not ensure your being chosen.  Mr. Steele will choose chaperones from that list.


Sweet Music Auction:  Currently set for Feb. 28, but that date could change.


Treasurer:  Michele Cloer has stepped down, Mrs. Jennings will take over those duties for the rest of the school year.


Basketball Concession:  Please stay and help clean up at the end of your shift.  We have had an issue with students leaving before the concession stand has been closed down.  Stay until all the work is done.

Charms: The middle school and high school bands use the Charms system online to keep all the students information and to communicate within the organization. Please take time to login and update yours and your student’s info if you have not done so already. post_text: We usually try to do a send off for those competing in Cross Country. Our plan was to go outside, run the first half of the drill and then when the cross country bus was leaving we would play the fight song. Well....they tricked us, they left in the Yukon instead of a bus and we didn't know until someone yelled "GO, Band!".... So we turned and played the fight song for them. Hopefully they could hear a little of it.

post_text:
The White Oak HS Band will be marching in the UIL Region 4 Marching Band Contest today, at Mt. Pleasant. Our scheduled performance time is at 2:45pm. We know that many of you that would like to be there cannot attend so we have another option for you. The marching contest will be streamed live online. I have posted a link below that will allow you to go directly to the live feed during the day of contest.

The contest officials work to keep the event on time, but there are times where it may be behind or ahead of schedule. Just to be safe, we would suggest you go ahead and start the live feed at 2:30. This way if we are running ahead of schedule you won't miss the performance. Our entire performance from setup/performance/exit will only take up 10 minutes at the most. We hope you can watch the live feed and we thank you for your support of the White Oak Band Program.

Click the following link: http://www.teamline.cc/free_view?teamcode=5428&eventcode=59&status=UUF

post_text:
Tonight our annual Fall Preview will be held at the practice field at 7:00. Due to the size of our band this year it may run a little longer than normal but it will be well worth the time. The band will perform some of the music they have learned this summer along with the Majorettes and Flags.

We are also very excited tonight to accept and send on our ALS challenge. The band was issued the challenge and is going to accept it in an epic way. If you are in band come dressed in something you won’t mind getting wet in. All we’ll say is; It involves a fire truck!

The students have worked extremely well this year so far and we are very proud of everything they have done. We are looking forward to another great year!

post_text:
Parents and Students involved in the WOISD Band Program,

We would like to invite you to a Post-UIL Concert featuring the High School Wind Ensemble and Symphonic Band next Monday evening at 6:30 in the evening. The concert will be in the Simmons Auditorium located on White Oak Road between the Cafeteria and High School.

The High School students have been working very hard on these contest pieces (over three months) and we would like to give you the opportunity to listen to these great pieces. Many of you are unable to get off of work and hear first-hand the direct result of the student's hard work at contest and we understand that. If you are the parent of a student in 6th, 7th, or 8th grade we would especially like to invite you to attend and see the result of your student's future work in the program. If you have any questions please contact Mr. Steele.

Thank you for your time and we hope to see you there.

steelej@woisd.net
903-291-2025
Jason Steele
Director of Bands
White Oak ISD

post_text:
***Sweet Music Concert and Auction Date Change****

We learned after we set our original date for this event that we had a high number of middle school students gone on a choir trip on Saturday and HS UIL academic events on the same day as well.

Also on the 2nd the directors and students wouldn't be able to begin setup because we would be gone with the 7th grade band to contest all day. Since we found those conflicts we've been searching for a date that doesn't compromise our end of the year spring concerts as well.

The event will take place on May 10th. Please update your calendars as this is the biggest fundraiser for the entire band program each year. We apologize for the inconvenience and will be going to a much earlier date next year.

If you still have a conflict email us a "woband@woisd.net"

post_text:
We hope you had a wonderful Christmas and will have an even better New Year. To celebrate the holidays, Mr. Whatley and Mr. Cartwright were joined by 6 students to perform at TubaChristmas. This event was held in Dallas at Thanksgiving Square. Basically, TubaChristmas is an event where Tuba and Euphonium players from all over come to perform Christmas music. This is all done with a one hour rehearsal and then the performance begins. This year the event had over 210 performers playing for more than 600 spectators.

We hope you enjoy our video linked below as we wish you a Merry Christmas and end with Wishing you a Happy New Year. We all thank you for your continued support.

Thank You

*Be sure to change the video quality to 1080p for a better video*

http://youtu.be/jBRLZdAm44I

shared_text:
Eddie Shuttlesworth
October 27, 2013 at 8:55 AM ·

A priceless moment. We are warming up for the Troup game last Friday night. We are wearing our camo uniforms, looking good and playing good. Into Roughneck stadium marches the best AA marching band in this area, in stride and in cadence. Led by the flags, marching to the rhythm of the drumline's beat, they just kept coming. The feeling of pride as a teacher, a coach, and a parent was overwhelming. I've often thought to myself, is this heaven, and then I realize, no, this is White Oak, Texas

Brains have been melted. 7/8 marching, 2 rotations, left foot on yardline, then right foot on yardline, 1 off hash then on hash. Don't forget the full band countermarch in 7/8. And we weren't able to play a single note because of how hard it is. We still need to get the second strain on the field with the giant "X" with flip flop to the rears.

BUT...... They are gonna get it. I can feel it!

Dress Code for Public Wreath Ceremony:

For Men: A combination of collared shirt (dress or polo) trousers, (khaki, blue, green, brown, or black) with a belt and appropriate shoes. A coat or tie is optional.

For Women: A reasonable length skirt (knee length) or trousers of a non-jean material combined with a top that covers the shoulders and appropriate dress shoes. An informal dress with appropriate skirt length is also acceptable.

NOT ACCEPTABLE:

Blue Jeans
Ripped Clothing
Athletic Wear
Patched Pants
Shorts of Any Kind
Tee Shirts
Tank Tops
Halter Tops
Tube Tops
Underwear as Outerwear
Shirts that expose the midriff
Miniskirts
Sneakers
Open Toed Shoes (Nice sandals during warmer months for women are appropriate)

post_text:
The White Oak Band program made school history today. The concert band was split into two separate competing groups this year. A Wind Ensemble directed by Jason Steele and a Symphonic Band directed by Jacovia Cartwright.

Today, both bands brought home sweepstakes trophies. These bands both received all first division ratings from the three concert judges and the three sight-reading judges. This is a first and White Oak is the only 2A band program that is large enough to have two complete competing groups. Congratulations to all of our students and a big thanks for their hard work. The directors are extremely proud of both bands and are very honored to be working with such quality students, administration, school board and community members. Thank You for everything you do to make the jobs we have enjoyable, and memorable.

-WO Band Directors

post_text: Just a quick FYI. After speaking with the Superintendent, Mr. Michael Gilbert, we are in a three way tie for first place in the Lone Star Cup standings. He also informed me that a large part of it was due to the fact that the HS Band's points from the State Marching Contest carried over to this year also. Without those, he said, we would be behind. Way to go Band! And also with the events we have coming up this Spring it looks like we could be champs for a second time. Go Necks!

post_text: The White Oak Band is now accepting applications for MS Twirling and Flag Sponsor. Please send resumes to Mr. Steele at the High School or Mr. Whatley at the Middle School. We will accept applications until February 12, 2013. You can email steelej@woisd.net or whatleyr@woisd.net if you have any questions or to email your resume. You may also call 903-291-2025 at the HS or 903-291-2060 MS.
